<DESCRIPT>  LOS-ANGELES; NEW-YORK; PROFESSIONAL; FOOTBALL; PLAYOFF; GAME; CHART  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  Kickoff: 9:30 a.m., Rich Stadium, Orchard Park, N.Y.; Line: Buffalo is favored
by 7 points.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  L.A. RAIDERS VS. BUFFALO BILLS  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  NFL Championships
AFC Championship Game
Charts attached to the end of this article  </MEMO>
<TEXT>  Television/radio: Ch 3 4 /KCBS (740).; Raiders update: Los Angeles is coming
off its first playoff appearance in five years -- a 20-10 victory over the
Bengals -- but the Raiders don't know if RB Bo Jackson will be able to play
against Bills. RB Marcus Allen figures to be the main offensive threat behind
a vastly improved offensive line. The teams have combined for 50 or more
points in their past four meetings, including the Bills' 38-24 victory Oct. 7
at Rich Stadium. Although they blew a 24-14 lead in the fourth quarter of that
game, the Raiders can look back and see some good things -- they controlled
the ball for more than 39 minutes and outgained the Bills 347 yards to 280.
The team's strength is its defense, which allowed a league-low four rushing
touchdowns this season and totaled 48 sacks, second best to Kansas City.;
Bills update: Buffalo is hosting its first championship game since 1966, but
this is the first at Rich Stadium, where the Bills are the NFL's only unbeaten
home team (9-0). The most prolific offense in the NFL (428 points) centers on
the versatility of RB Thurman Thomas, the game-breaking skills of WRs Andre
Reed and James Lofton, an excellent line anchored by C Kent Hull and OT Will
Wolford, and the matured leadership of QB Jim Kelly, who is coming off his
best NFL season and is recovered from a knee injury that sidelined him for 2
1/2 games. Buffalo's defense ranked fifth in the AFC and boasts one of the
league's best front seven, including DE Bruce Smith (19 sacks) and LBs
Cornelius Bennett, Shane Conlan and Darryl Talley.; Key injuries: Raiders --
RB Bo Jackson (hip) is doubtful; S Eddie Anderson (calf), DE Howie Long
(hand), CB Lionel Washington (hamstring) are probable. Bills -- None.; Bills
